OMNI-SHOGUN: Technical Specification v1.0
Project Code: Fortress Edition (Tokyo 2026)
Lead Architect: Liban Ahmed Egal
Network: Sui Blockchain (Sui Move 2024.1)
 
1. Executive Summary
The OMNI-SHOGUN protocol is a high-performance, object-centric security architecture built on the Sui Network. It bridges the gap between biological telemetry and digital assets through the SHOI (Sovereign Human-Object Integration) protocol. The system is designed to achieve a theoretical throughput of 297,450 TPS with sub-second finality, providing a secure foundation for human-on-chain evolution.
2. Core Architecture Components
2.1 SHOI Protocol (Sovereign Human-Object Integration)
The SHOI protocol establishes a persistent, immutable link between a human user and their digital representative (Warrior NFT). Unlike legacy static NFTs, SHOI assets are dynamic—evolving and reacting based on real-time biometric and physical inputs from the user.
2.2 PoPE Consensus (Proof-of-Physical-Effort)
PoPE is a novel consensus mechanism that validates digital asset evolution through verified physical exertion.
•	Core Formula:
$$E = \sum_{i=1}^{n} (P_i \cdot \omega) + (B \cdot \delta)$$
(Where $E$ is Evolution, $P_i$ is Kinetic Force, $\omega$ is the weight coefficient, $B$ is Biometric Heart Rate, and $\delta$ is the consistency factor).
•	Data Integrity: Physical data is ingested via IoT sensors and secured using Zero-Knowledge Proofs (ZKP) to ensure user privacy while preventing data spoofing or fraudulent inputs.
2.3 Zen-Equilibrium Engine
The Zen-Equilibrium Engine acts as the security hardening layer. It is specifically designed for Sybil Resistance, monitoring transaction patterns to ensure the network remains balanced and resilient against bot-driven congestion or automated spamming.
3. Technical Implementation
•	Programming Language: Sui Move 2024.1
•	Execution Model: Parallel Transaction Execution (Sui-native)
•	Latency/Finality: ~390ms (Real-time responsiveness)
•	Target Infrastructure: Mission-critical deployment for Tokyo 2026.
4. Security Hardening & Economic Logic
•	Rate-Limiting: Implemented at the individual object level to mitigate spam and DDoS-style attacks within the network.
•	Hon-or Decay Invariant: To maintain economic scarcity and incentive alignment, inactivity triggers an automated decay in asset rank.
o	Decay Formula: $f(x) = H_{initial} \cdot e^{-\lambda t}$
•	Audibility: All mathematical logic and state transitions are executed on-chain via Smart Contracts, allowing for transparent third-party auditing and verification.

